The paper deals with the problem of scheduling transmitters subjected to interference constraints, which is a common problem in wireless communication networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The problem also involves optimization and binary programming, which suggests categories such as cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The problem is also relevant to networked systems, which suggests categories such as cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
